All these smells are incomplete or incorrect application of object-oriented programming principles.

Switch
ğŸ’Š Treatment 
As a rule of thumb, when you see switch you should think of polymorphism.

Alternative Classes with Different Interfaces
Two classes perform identical functions but have different method names.
ğŸ’Š Treatment 
If only part of the functionality of the classes is duplicated, try using Extract Superclass.
In this case, the existing classes will become subclasses.